# Copy to .env.local (dev) or set in your deployment environment.

# Interim API access secret. When set, every /api route requires this value,
# presented as either `Authorization: Bearer <secret>` or a `psap_access` cookie.
#   - REQUIRED in production: if unset in production the API fails closed (503),
#     so a deployed instance is never accidentally open.
#   - Optional in local dev: if unset, auth is bypassed locally for convenience.
# This is a placeholder until Microsoft Entra (OIDC) is wired in — see SECURITY.md.
# Generate a strong value, e.g.:  openssl rand -base64 32
APP_ACCESS_SECRET=
